# Day 3 - Linux Lab Notes

## Lab 1 - Input and Output Redirection

### Redirect Output

```bash
ls > files.txt
```

### Append Output

```bash
echo "Linux" >> files.txt
```

### Redirect Errors

```bash
ls invalid_directory 2> errors.txt
```

### Redirect Output and Errors

```bash
ls existing invalid > output.txt 2>&1
```

---

## Lab 2 - Null Device

Ignore unwanted output

```bash
ls existing invalid > /dev/null 2>&1
```

---

## Lab 3 - Compare Files

Create two files

```bash
touch file1 file2
```

Compare

```bash
diff file1 file2
cmp file1 file2
sdiff file1 file2
```

---

## Lab 4 - Environment Variables

Display variables

```bash
printenv
```

Check HOME

```bash
echo $HOME
```

Create variable

```bash
NAME="Ram"
```

Export variable

```bash
export NAME
```

Verify

```bash
echo $NAME
```

---

## Lab 5 - Process Management

Display running processes

```bash
ps
```

Real-time monitor

```bash
top
```

Process tree

```bash
pstree
```

---

## Lab 6 - Background Processes

Run command in background

```bash
sleep 100 &
```

List jobs

```bash
jobs
```

Bring to foreground

```bash
fg
```

Send back to background

```bash
bg
```

---

## Lab 7 - Kill Process

Start a process

```bash
sleep 100
```

Find PID

```bash
ps
```

Terminate

```bash
kill PID
```

Force terminate

```bash
kill -9 PID
```

---

## Lab 8 - Exit Status

Check previous command status

```bash
echo $?
```

Exit with success

```bash
exit 0
```

Exit with failure

```bash
exit 1
```

